FBI director
and had this kind of a
conversation.

26:07.799 --> 26:12.437 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GEORGE TERWILLIGER: Judy, I
think one of the
things we have to keep in mind
is the concept

26:12.470 --> 26:18.810 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of the independence of FBI from
the authority
of the attorney general and
indeed from the

26:18.843 --> 26:26.484 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
president is not quite the
premise that some
believe and that perhaps Jim
Comey operated

26:26.518 --> 26:28.320 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
on.

26:28.353 --> 26:32.490 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If you think back to the days of
J. Edgar
Hoover, J. Edgar Hoover had a
lot of independence

26:32.524 --> 26:37.329 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
from the Justice Department and
from presidents,
and it resulted in a very
unhealthy situation.

26:37.362 --> 26:40.398 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And, in fact,
Comey raised
the name of J. Edgar Hoover
today.

26:40.432 --> 26:42.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GEORGE TERWILLIGER: I heard
that.

26:42.334 --> 26:45.837 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, perhaps the
biggest question,
one of the biggest questions
swirling around,

26:45.870 --> 26:51.009 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
